Long Island ’s hockey team the
Islanders are to get a new arena, said  New York ’s Nassau County
Executive Edward Mangano at a press conference today.  The sports complex will include a baseball stadium and will
replace Nassau Coliseum, he said. The proposed development will
go to a referendum planned for Aug. 1.  To contact the reporter on this story:
